ygData.subject: RE: [eqenchanters] Where to go...
ygData.msgSnippet: Shadow Med. Levels 24-26, warrior, necro, and clerics. Need a good group at your level, but the fights are fast, intense, and fun (plus good xp). South Karana
ygData.messageBody:
Shadow Med. Levels 24-26, warrior, necro, and clerics. Need a good group at
your level, but the fights are fast, intense, and fun (plus good xp).

South Karana Aviaks or Centaurs.

North Karana maybe.

Rathe Mountain Cyclops groups soon. Giant Skeleton groups right now would be
fine.

I hear Cazic Thule is awesome in the 20s and 30s.

-Leod, 50 shaman, Fennin Ro
-Dysin, 30 Enchanter, Fennin Ro

PS. For me, I was at Shadow Men in a groupo of two having a friend pull,
from 22-27, then moved to Centaurs from 27-30, now I'm in Paw.



-----Original Message-----
From: Jenni [mailto:freya@...]
Sent: March 27, 2000 10:09 AM
To: eqenchanters@onelist.com
Subject: [eqenchanters] Where to go...


From: Jenni <freya@...>

Hi guys!

I'm real close to lvl 24 now and I'm wondering where I should be fighting.
I'm loving permafrost, but I want to move on soon. (Don't even say
Highkeep, I hate that place.. :) ). I checked out Sol A, but there
weren't enough people there at the time that could group with me (mostly
lvl 35 and up). the mobs there looked great, and I found a couple nice
places to set up camp, but it might be tough to get a group going in that
situation. Any other suggestions? I'm really loving the dungeon scene.
big pulls, mez, and tons of exp and good loot. Anybody have any favorite
dungeons that would be good for my level? :)

Thanks!
Ezrae Dreamstealer
Lvl 23 DE Enchantress
Brell Serilis
